<div class="cover">
  <div class="sub">Almadar &nbsp;·&nbsp; Information Security Policy</div>
  <h1>Information Security Policy for Almadar</h1>
  <div class="ref">POL-ISP-001 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Version 1.0 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Internal — Confidential</div>
</div>

<h2>1. Document Control</h2>
<table class="meta">
  <tr>
    <td class="lbl">Reference</td><td>POL-ISP-001</td>
    <td class="lbl">Version</td><td>1.0</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="lbl">Effective</td><td>2025-03-01</td>
    <td class="lbl">Next Review</td><td>2026-03-01</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="lbl">Owner</td><td>Chief Information Security Officer</td>
    <td class="lbl">Approver</td><td>Chief Executive Officer</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="lbl">Classification</td><td>Internal — Confidential</td>
    <td class="lbl">Framework</td><td>ISO 27001:2022</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>2. Purpose</h2>
<p>This policy exists to protect Almadar's information assets from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, modification, or destruction. It ensures the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of our information systems and data.</p>

<h2>3. Scope</h2>
<p>This policy applies to all Almadar employees, contractors, and third-party vendors who access or handle Almadar's information systems and data. It covers all Almadar information systems, including but not limited to, networks, servers, workstations, mobile devices, and cloud services.</p>

<h2>4. Roles & Responsibilities</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th style="width:32%">Role</th>
    <th>Responsibility</th>
  </tr>
  
    <tr>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;font-weight:bold;width:32%;background:#f8fafc;vertical-align:top;">Chief Information Security Officer</td>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;vertical-align:top;">Developing, implementing, and maintaining this policy</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;font-weight:bold;width:32%;background:#f8fafc;vertical-align:top;">Information Security Manager</td>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;vertical-align:top;">Coordinating information security activities and ensuring compliance with this policy</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;font-weight:bold;width:32%;background:#f8fafc;vertical-align:top;">System Administrators</td>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;vertical-align:top;">Implementing and maintaining information systems security controls</td>
    </tr>
</table>

<h2>5. Policy Statements</h2>
<div class="notice">
  All statements are mandatory. SHALL and MUST indicate required actions; MUST NOT indicates prohibited actions.
</div>

    <h3 style="color:#1B3A6B;font-size:12pt;margin:14pt 0 5pt;padding-bottom:3pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
      5. 5.1 User Access Management
    </h3>
    <ul style="margin:0 0 10pt;padding-left:18pt;">
      <li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">All users SHALL have unique accounts.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Privileged access MUST be approved by the CISO.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Shared accounts MUST NOT be used.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="color:#1B3A6B;font-size:12pt;margin:14pt 0 5pt;padding-bottom:3pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
      6. 5.2 Password Management
    </h3>
    <ul style="margin:0 0 10pt;padding-left:18pt;">
      <li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Passwords MUST be at least 12 characters long.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Passwords MUST be changed every 90 days.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Password reuse MUST NOT occur.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="color:#1B3A6B;font-size:12pt;margin:14pt 0 5pt;padding-bottom:3pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
      7. 5.3 Network Security
    </h3>
    <ul style="margin:0 0 10pt;padding-left:18pt;">
      <li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Firewalls MUST be configured to allow only necessary traffic.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Intrusion detection and prevention systems MUST be implemented.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Network segmentation MUST be implemented.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="color:#1B3A6B;font-size:12pt;margin:14pt 0 5pt;padding-bottom:3pt;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
      8. 5.4 Data Backup and Recovery
    </h3>
    <ul style="margin:0 0 10pt;padding-left:18pt;">
      <li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Data backups MUST be performed daily.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Data backups MUST be stored offsite.</li><li style="margin-bottom:4pt;line-height:1.65;">Data recovery procedures MUST be tested quarterly.</li>
    </ul>

<h2>Framework Alignment</h2>
<p><strong>ISO 27001:2022:</strong> This policy satisfies the following ISO 27001:2022 controls: A.5.1.1 (Information security policies), A.5.1.2 (Information security organization), and A.12.6.1 (Network security).</p>

<h2>Exceptions</h2>
<p>Exceptions to this policy MUST be requested in writing and approved by the CISO.</p>

<h2>Enforcement</h2>
<p>Violations of this policy will result in disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment.</p>

<h2>Definitions</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th style="width:28%">Term</th>
    <th>Definition</th>
  </tr>
  
    <tr>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;font-weight:bold;width:28%;background:#f8fafc;vertical-align:top;">Confidentiality</td>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;vertical-align:top;">The protection of information from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, modification, or destruction.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;font-weight:bold;width:28%;background:#f8fafc;vertical-align:top;">Integrity</td>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;vertical-align:top;">The accuracy, completeness, and reliability of information.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;font-weight:bold;width:28%;background:#f8fafc;vertical-align:top;">Availability</td>
      <td style="padding:6pt 10pt;border:1pt solid #d1d5db;vertical-align:top;">The accessibility and usability of information systems and data.</td>
    </tr>
</table>

